Subtitle
14
15 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING STATUTORY
16 BONDING REQUIREMENTS FOR CONSTRUCTION
17 PROJECTS OF THE STATE HIGHWAY
18 COMMISSION.
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
21
22 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 27-67-206(f) and (g), concerning new
23 construction projects of the State Highway Commission, are amended to read as
24 follows:
25 (f) Successful bidders shall be required to furnish a surety bond or
26 bonds by a surety company to be approved by the commission, in a penal sum of
27 at least one-fourth (¼) of the amount of the contract price, conditioned as
28 the commission may require to ensure that each contract between a bidder and
29 the commission is fully executed and completed and that the bond or bonds
30 fully cover the exposure of the state.
31 (g) However, the commission may accept personal bonds, but in every
32 case in which a personal bond is accepted, the contractor shall be required
33 to deposit United States Government bonds, state highway bonds or notes, or
34 valid bonds of any road improvement district referred to in Acts 1929, No.
35 65, § 19 [repealed], in an amount equal to twenty-five percent (25%) of the
36 amount of the contract to be held in escrow as collateral security for the
